# Compute resources available for heavy workloads (gitignored — copy to .env and edit).
#
# Used by builders/agents to pick a remote host for sweeps, evolution, Nash
# analysis, training runs, and anything else CLAUDE.md flags as "❌ NEVER Run
# Locally". The list is dynamic: hosts come and go (cloud rentals, lab
# clusters, personal machines). Update .env as your inventory changes.
#
# Format: one host alias per line. Leave empty / commented out if unavailable.
# Agents should `source .env`, prefer the first non-empty option in priority
# order, and verify the host actually resolves (`ssh -o BatchMode=yes
# -o ConnectTimeout=5 $HOST echo ok`) before launching work.
#
# Conventions:
# - HOST aliases must match an entry in ~/.ssh/config (or be a resolvable
#   hostname). Don't put credentials here.
# - Annotate each host with a short note: CPU vs GPU class, parallelism, repo
#   path on the remote, and any provisioning quirks.

# Personal / lab hosts ---------------------------------------------------------

# Robb's Mac Studio (M-series, CPU-bound workloads, repo at ~/GitHub/bucket-brigade)
COMPUTE_HOST_PRIMARY=robbs-mac-studio

# alc cluster (RTX 4090 + 32 cores; env is CPU-bound so GPU buys little, but
# parallelism is the win). Substitute a specific node name (alc-1, alc-2, ...).
COMPUTE_HOST_CLUSTER=

# Cloud rentals (rented per-experiment) ----------------------------------------

# Lambda Labs instance (GPU on demand). Set the SSH alias once provisioned.
COMPUTE_HOST_LAMBDA=

# GCP instance (typically n2d-highcpu-* for CPU sweeps or a2-* for GPU).
COMPUTE_HOST_GCP=

# Notes ------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# Provisioning gotchas for any fresh host (see CLAUDE.md → COMPUTE RESOURCE
# GUIDELINES for the canonical setup checklist):
#   - Non-interactive SSH PATH is bare on macOS; prepend
#     `export PATH="/opt/homebrew/bin:$HOME/.cargo/bin:$PATH"` in scripted commands.
#   - uv creates venvs without pip; run `uv pip install pip` before
#     `python -m pip install -e ./bucket-brigade-core --no-build-isolation`.
#   - Rust build env: `PYO3_USE_ABI3_FORWARD_COMPATIBILITY=1`, unset `RUSTC_WRAPPER`.
